**Special Containment Procedures:**
No items or personnel are to enter or exit SCP-1744 or the external containment area without approval by Site Command. Anything entering SCP-1744 must be examined both before and after contact. Anything exiting SCP-1744 is to be contained and examined; contaminated objects or resistance by any Personnel during the process will be detained by guard personnel and escorted to Site Command. Any staff enteringSCP-1744 must be equipped with a long-range GPS tracking device. Staff personnel entering SCP-1744 are to don radioactive resistant HazMat gear. As well as a SIAR, (Standard Issue Automatic Rifle.) Staff is prohibited to go into SCP-1744 Alone. Failure to obey this command brings a higher percentage of MIA or KIA status. Site command isn’t responsible for any of the lost or killed personnel that fail to comply, they will be deemed insubordinate. Groups should be no less than three and shouldn’t exceed eight persons per group. Should staff become separated, [DATA EXPUNGED], thereof they are to immediately exit SCP-1744. Any personnel that has been contaminated by the Radioactive fallout due to bite scratch or breathed the air for more than 3 hours should report to site 354 for [DATA EXPUNGED]staff or equipment lost within SCP-1744 are to be declared “missing” 48 hours after loss of GPS contact. Staff or equipment located after disappearance of GPS contacts are to be recovered whenever possible. Should the GPS beacon [DATA EXPUNGED]. --Is 30 kilometers designated for evacuation and placed under military control.--
**UPDATE:** Exclusion Zone covers an area of approximately 2,600 kilometers due to outbreak during patrol 3.

**Background:** SCP-1744 is a result of what was a catastrophic nuclear accident that occurred on 26 April 1986 at the ████████ Nuclear Power Plant in Ukraine

**Description:** An explosion and fire released large quantities of radioactive particles into the atmosphere, reaching for miles. The disaster is widely considered to have been the worst nuclear power plant accident in history, and is one of only two classified as a level 7 event on the International Nuclear Event Scale. The disaster began during a systems test on Saturday, 26 April 1986 at reactor number four of the ██████ plant, which is near the city of██████ and in proximity to the administrative border with ██████and the ██████River. There was a sudden and unexpected power surge, and when an emergency shutdown was attempted, an exponentially larger spike in power output occurred, which led to a reactor vessel rupture and a series of steam explosions. These events exposed the graphite moderator of the reactor to air, causing it to ignite. The resulting fire sent a plume of highly radioactive fallout into the atmosphere and over an extensive geographical area, including████. Due to the radioactive fallout in SCP-1744 hundreds of the civilians that weren’t able to leave during the evacuation became sick, the radioactive compound made many of the survivors mutate and become deformed.
[[div style=]]
|||| [[image http://cdn.c.photoshelter.com/img-get/I0000tQ6MMz1ctdg/s/900/ukraine-chernobyl-zone-UA100126.jpg width=]] ||
||||~ the city of ██████population of roughly 49,000 before evacuation, now around 35,000 infected still in the site ||
[[/div]]
**City of ██████**
Named for the nearby ██████ River, ██████ was founded on 4 February 1970, the ninth nuclear city in the Soviet Union, for the ████████ Nuclear Power Plant. It was officially proclaimed a city in 1979, and had grown to a population of roughly 49,000. Access to ██████, unlike cities of military importance, was not restricted before the disaster as nuclear power stations were seen by the Soviet Union as safer than other types of power plants. Nuclear power stations were presented as being an achievement of Soviet engineering, where nuclear power was harnessed for peaceful projects.

**Nuclear fallout Disaster**
The disaster began during a systems test on Saturday, 26 April 1986 at reactor number four of the ███████plant, which is near the city of ██████ and in proximity to the administrative border with██████ and the █████ River. There was a sudden and unexpected power surge, and when an emergency shutdown was attempted, an exponentially larger spike in power output occurred, which led to a reactor vessel rupture and a series of steam explosions. These events exposed the graphite moderator of the reactor to air, causing it to ignite. The resulting fire sent a plume of highly radioactive fallout into the atmosphere and over an extensive geographical area, including ██████.

On 26 April 1986, at 01:23, reactor four suffered a catastrophic power increase, leading to explosions in its core. This dispersed large quantities of radioactive fuel and core materials into the atmosphere [23]:73 and ignited the combustible graphite moderator. The burning graphite moderator increased the emission of radioactive particles, carried by the smoke, as the reactor had not been encased by any kind of hard containment vessel. The accident occurred during an experiment scheduled to test a potential safety emergency core cooling feature, which took place during a normal shutdown procedure.

**Evacuation Failure**
On 26 April 1986 1:28 the city was under siege by the Soviet military. Evacuation starts for the next forty-eight hours, during the fiftieth hour the radioactive fallout became thick. The smoke and debris from the exploded plant littered the city in a large black plume of toxic air and poison. The mutation started, hundreds of the oncoming citizens began to mutate. The military was ordered to seal off any exits and to terminate any of the infected people. During the elimination process, most of the guards became sick due to the toxic air witch was able to penetrate the standard gas mask. A mass panic of armed guards and infected citizens erupted in to the late night.
At 12:48 the city was sealed off from the public and the Exclusion Zone was set.

Note: The city was undergoing evacuation for 3 day when the Soviet Union called off the evacuation due to radioactive fallout becoming fatal within 52 hours of the operation.

**Death Toll**
There is no set number of infected or dead citizens due.
250 MIA soldiers (estimate)
450 Infected soldiers deemed KIA. (Estimate)

**Mutation and birth defects**

,,diseases associated with Radioactive Fallout,,
* All cancers
* Non-malignant thyroid nodular disease
* Parathyroid adenoma
* Posterior subscapular cataracts
* Tumors of the brain and central nervous system

Side-affects
• Loss of hair
• Skin becomes yellow-white and or green yellow-white
• Skin bruises easily
• Tumors full of toxic waste form all over body
o Common areas are face, neck, and chest
• Skin tends to burn when in direct sunlight

**Addendum SCP-XXXX-01**

[[collapsible show=]]
[__**Test A-1 - 21 June 1986**__
 **Subject:** Reentering SCP-XXXX
 **Procedure:** Group of class-D personnel (3) Equipped with HazMat Suits and gas masks (Class 3), military issued backpack with flashlight, matches, two days’ worth of MRE's. An SIAR with 3 magazines of ammunition and an state-of-the-art helmet cam (first of its kind). Entered at 00:01
 **Results:** All class-D personnel were deemed MIA after entering the apartment building 23. Class-D personnel were unable to fire off their weapons, were dragged into the building and were not seen again. Video record was damaged during dragging of class-D personnel down a flight of stairs. Video record lasted 34 minutes before video was cut due to lack of visual or audio.
 **Analysis:** Failed Attempt. SCP-1744 occupants were not hostile till the first team of Class-D personnel got close to them. Once the occupants noticed that they were not infected they were brutally beat to death as well of [DATA EXPUNGED]. SCP-1744 occupants can only be seen in the windows of the building or in dark areas of the city of ██████ during the day. Which SCP-1744 is located nearby which is include into SCP-1744 because of the Radioactive Fallout.]
[[/collapsible]]

[[collapsible show=]]
[__**Test A-2 - 23 June 1986**__
 **Subject:** Search And Recover
 **Procedure:** Eight men team of four level 4 staff and four Class-D (trained in combat) Equipped with HazMat Suits and gas masks (Class 3), military issued backpack with flashlight, matches, two days’ worth of MRE's. An SIAR with 3 magazines of ammunition and a state-of-the-art helmet cam (first of its kind). Entered at 03:00
 **Operation:**
 *03:05*: Group 2 entered SCP-1744 in a armored black van.
 *03:10*: Pulled up to building 23. (no sight of occupants or Former Class-D Personnel)
 *03:14*: Entered the building.
 *03:15*: Load screaming noises are heard.
 *03:16*: Start down the stair well. (Former group was seen dragged down)
 *03:19*: Becomes too dark to see, Switches to flash lights.
 *03:21*: Reach the bottom of stair well, blood is spotted beginning down the last five stairs (Screams seize and becomes quiet)
 *03:26*: Starts to follow blood trail.
 *03:29*: Reach a doubled door doorway, radios' command for permission to continue on mission.
 *03:30*: Permission is granted.
 *03:30.4*: One of Class-D personnel trips over former Class-D's Helmet cam.
 *details*: Camera power LED turns from red to green (as if it was turned on) Group checks with Command if power was restore.
 *03:34*: Command denies any restoring of power to camera.
 *03:38*: Faint cries from behind the double doors become audible.
 doors are lock and covered in blood.
 *03:42*: Doors are breached and continue on mission.
 *03:44*: Former class-D personnel bodies are found.(mangled)
 *03:45*: Deafening screams fill the room and SCP-1744 occupants emerge surrounding them.
 *03:45.7*: Group 2 starts to begin termination of hostile occupants as they retreat to the stair well.
 *03:47*: Group 2 retreats up and out of the apartment building.
 *03:50* Meanwhile contacting command A large cry echoes throughout the town alerting SCP-1744's occupants in neighboring builds.
 *03:50.5* Request to fast extract is sent to command.
 *03:51* Request is denied.
 [DATA EXPUNGED]
 *08:00* Group is recovered.
 **Results:** Operation is successful.
 **Analysis:** Two class-D personnel and one level four guard was killed during the operation.
